text: Habrosyne dieckmanni is a moth in the family Drepanidae. It is found in the Russian Far East, Japan, north-eastern China (Heilongjiang, Jilin) and Korea. The larvae feed on Rubus species.A review of the Thyatirin-moths (Lepidoptera, Drepanidae: Thyatirinae) of the Russian Far East ==References== Category:Thyatirinae Category:Moths described in 1888
title: Habrosyne dieckmanni
